    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan for `Bun.INI`. Let me summarize the key findings and what needs to be done:\n\n## What already exists\n\n- **`src/ini.zig`** — A complete INI `Parser` with sections (`[section]`), `key=value` pairs, `;`/`#` comments, dotted keys, arrays (`key[]`), quoted values, and env-var expansion. **No new parser logic is needed.**\n- **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — 625+ lines of tests already exist for the internal API. These stay untouched.\n\n## 7 files to create/modify\n\n| # | Action | File |\n|---|--------|------|\n| 1 | **Create** | `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` |\n| 2 | **Edit** | `src/bun.js/api.zig` — add `pub const INIObject = @import(...)` |\n| 3 | **Edit** | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — 4 insertions (lazy callback, `@export`, getter fn, import) |\n| 4 | **Edit** | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER` |\n| 5 | **Edit** | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — add one row to the property table |\n| 6 | **Edit** | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` — add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` |\n| 7 | **Create** | `test/js/bun/ini/bun-ini.test.ts` — public API tests |\n\n## Key implementation decisions\n\n- **`parse()`** just calls the existing `ini.Parser` identically to how `IniTestingAPIs.parse` does it (passing `globalThis.bunVM().transpiler.env` for the env loader).\n- **`stringify()`** is new — uses `jsc.JSPropertyIterator` (same as `JSON5Object.zig`) to walk properties, emitting scalars first then nested objects as `[section]` blocks.\n- No `src/interchange/` file needed — `src/ini.zig` is the parser and it already lives at the right level.",
